  "body": "This adds the ability to ingest Github pushes and pull requests from the exchanges populated by the `taskcluster-github` project.\n\nThis follows a very similar pattern to the Pulse job ingestion:\n- Adds a management command called `read_pulse_resultsets` which populates a queue called `store_pulse_resultsets`.  Then the celery task will process those messages\n- For each message, we need more information than is in the Pulse message (namely the revisions).  So we must call the Github api to get that information.\n\nStill needed:\n- taskcluster-github needs to include the base sha for pushes so I can get only the pertinent commits from github\n- I will probably need to add a branch name to the `Repository` table so that I can distinguish which `gaia` or `bugzilla` repos it belongs to because they each share github repo urls, of course.\n\n<!-- Reviewable:start -->\n\n---\n\nThis change is [<img src=\"https://reviewable.io/review_button.svg\" height=\"34\" align=\"absmiddle\" alt=\"Reviewable\"/>](https://reviewable.io/reviews/mozilla/test_treeherder/1692)\n\n<!-- Reviewable:end -->\n",
